reviewText: If you think doulas are only for "rich" women, think again! This story shows the inspirational work of one amazing, committed doula who serves teen moms on Chicago's West Side. The real, down-to earth ways she provides emotional and physical support and information to each young woman, as well as their families and community as a whole, is a great model for anyone trying to work in community or to work with pregnant women. It could also be a great way to show pregnant teens examples of how empowering natural childbirth can be.
